rComments: Lectures are engaging and give you useful information (that comes up on exams almost verbatim!) while still being open to discussion/questions. He favours papers for grading, and as long as you listen to the lectures and keep up with the readings, the prompts are generally easy to work off of
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures ', 'Graded by few things', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Professor Lynch really cares about his students and the courses he teaches. He is more than happy to give extra help and is extremely quick with replying to emails. I have him for 2 classes this term and hes by FAR my favourite prof this year.
He really cares for his students and willing to spend extra time to help ESL learners.

My first impression was that this course would be a bit boring, but this prof genuinely loves the material and it didn't take long to get on his wavelength. For literary types, he is quite humorous, and he is very thorough in his professing. If you show up for class and pay attention and do the readings, this class is very straightforward.

You don't need to show up to class as long as you show up to the classes in which you must hand in your papers. He doesn't take attendance, and he's a really easy grader. Lynch places the most weight upon the essays.

Go to his lectures and you're golden when it comes to tests and papers. He has a lot of great things to say, and it directly correlates to the tests and assignments. Plus, he is a great speaker and is very clear- does not waste time.

The material is extremely uninteresting, as are the lectures. This is worsened by Lynchs lecture style, as he drones monotonously and explains to the point where the simplest story seems incomprehensible. Were it not for the fact that his class is mandatory I would never have stuck with it.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Mr Lynchs subtle humour and quick wit make the lectures a lot more engaging. He is well acquainted with the course material and able to make even more complex works seem straightforward. That being said, the works chosen can be difficult to understand without outside guidance, so regular attendance is recommend in order to do well in this class.

I took this course as an elective, and I'm so glad I did. He's really witty, and though there's a fair amount of course material to cover, he goes over all of it in-depth and tells you exactly what you need to know to do well. "Engaging with Lit." is an apt name for the course, as he is very engaging and makes students eager to engage, as well.

Prof. Lynch is amazing. His voice is monotone but he has a great sense of humour that more than makes up for it. Always glad to give you feedback on an essay outline. I hope I get to take more of his classes in the future.

He tells you what he wants, just pay attention and ask questions. The textbook (that he wrote) is a book of short stories and I highly recommend purchasing it (second hand, it's a lot cheaper). The novel (Oryx and Crake), I didn't purchase, nor did I read it but he talks in-depth about everything read. I recommend the book because you get it more.

A true gem! Prof. Lynch knows his stuff, and really puts lots of care into preparing his lectures. While he is a little more quiet and calm, he is also really funny. I missed a bunch of lectures this semester, but I still did really well because his expectations are so clear. Have had like 3 classes with him & would gladly take more!

Easily one of my favourite profs. He always brings a positive attitude to class and makes lectures interesting with his witty sense of humour + interesting analyses of the texts. He's a tough grader, but fair.

Lynch is probably my favourite professor so far because as a student I learned so much in his class, and enjoyed learning it. His lectures are funny, informative, and he makes everyone feel comfortable about answering in class. I had him for a year long class and was always excited to attend. Lynch is a hard marker when it comes to essays!

Held office hours for further clarity about the three essays. Should attend classes to know important terms for the final and to clarify the abundance of short stories. No tests but three essays and a final. Quiet lecturer that sometimes feel long. Overall, a very approachable professor but you will have to work hard and attend classes.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: Prof Lynch isn't a bad prof, just a little dull. He really cares about the technical aspects of the English language and essay writing but he has a really monotonous voice. He's really nice and tries to liven up class with jokes but they aren't usually that funny. He also marks pretty tough but is there to help when you ask for it. Don't recommend.
Good teacher. Very passionate about english. Tough grader but makes it very clear what he looks for in essays and his care for improvement.

Marking gets harder as you go along one reading a night. 3 essays and a final. Do NOT take a 3 hour with him or if you do make sure you have a laptop so you can do other stuff because otherwise you will die of boredom. His lectures are pretty general and he kinda goes all over the place so I dont think I really needed to go
Prof's expectations are clear, gives lots of constructive criticism. Not an easy marker, but fair. Attendance is mandatory in order to be prepared for the final.

Not an interesting speaker. Doesn't take constructive criticism or treat you like an adult. The syllabus is confusing as it lacks dates, and there's no opportunity to get ahead in the class without setting yourself back. He asks you to identify passages with little to no context and wants first names but doesn't put them on the syllabus. DON'T TAKE

One of the best profs I have ever had. He is extremely easy to understand and he takes the time to thoroughly analyze the course material. Midterms are easy if you take good notes and have a memory. Essays are graded fairly and if you put in any effort in this class, you will be rewarded.

I thought I would HATE Canadian Literature but he actually made me love it. His class was the best I've taken in my four years at the University. I would highly recommend him to anyone. Seriously, he is such a great Professor!

Totally one of the best profs at U of O, he knows what he is talking about, has a great sense of humor and gives excellent lectures. Makes efforts to learn names, pokes fun at himself (and you if he likes you). He's also extremely stylish (google sweater vests if you need to). Genuine
I hate Canadian Lit, but he made it as tolerable as possible. Very knowledgeable and witty. A wide array of sweater vests.

Brilliant mind. Very knowledgeable. Entertaining and fun. Makes it worth going to class. Knows his material inside and out.  Exams are straightforward and honest, exactly what he makes them out to be. Very helpful with essays or questions relevant to the topic. Does go on tangents a lot, but they're fun!

He's hilarious! Very knowledgeable, has a lot published on Canadian Lit, and a wonderful sense of humour. Isn't afraid to poke fun at the class or himself. Thoroughly enjoyable, and reading was easy to keep up with. Lectures are VERY detailed (so even if you don't do the readings you have a good sense about the poems/narratives). Can veer off-track
Best Prof. ever! Extremely knowledgeable and a great lecturer. He is also a fair marker. I hope I can take another course with him again someday.

This professor's style is more of the traditional lecturing style--nothing fancy, but I like that, and I enjoy listening to him talk because he is so thorough and knowledgeable. He doesn't leave me asking questions in the end. He covers material very thoroughly in class from different perspectives. The easiness part is subjective.
He's a smart guy but he'll lull you to sleep. Be prepared to take random notes and focus all your attention on paying attention

the class gets very boring and there is alot of reading (minimum one story per night) and its a good idea to take notes of all class lectures ! the exam was very straight foward and just like he told us it would be. he is an easy enough marker and if you attend class everyday and complete all essays you will do good for sure ! overall: good
Interesting...even if his hair is a little too reminiscent of Dwight Schrute. A bit of a low talker, but he knows his stuff. Makes dirty jokes sometimes...weird.
A god among men. take any course her offers
Awesome prof!! Loved his lectures. Knows anything and everything about Can. Lit. Great sense of humour, I would love to take any of his courses!
Amazing prof - would take anything with him! Cutest man, really encourages participation, brilliant
Funny and adorable like a teddy bear, I really enjoyed his class.  Perhaps not the most brilliant professor, but certainly knowledgeable and helpful.
Best class ever.

great prof. knows his stuff. inspires you to read, listen, learn. excellent lectures. he's got a great sense of humour, read the stories, and participate in class - he encourages you to do so. i would take any class with him. gives good feeback to improve your writing skills.
For "boring" read: "Didn't do the reading."
This man, while competent, is extremely boring.  His classes are an excellent place to get some solid daydreaming time in.  Good luck.
Funny, entertaining and knows what he's doing.

A great sense of humour - can make you laugh at yourself for being in English (because way to many people take themselves seriously in this program) always makes the material interesting (ok, most of the time)
Funny guy!  Be sure to do your readings and bring a sense of humor to class!
Sense of humor is great!
AMAZING!  Great sense of humor and a great lecturer.  Do your reading!
be prepared to take some ribbing... but he knows how to captivate an audience
Keep On Shining!
